    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @Metarei-network \r\n\r\nI'm currious about the usecase for this feature. Is something similar used in any live protocol?\r\nAlso, I'm worried that this is not really safe, as any transaction that passes the \"phrase\" is susceptible to being front-run.\r\n\r\nIMO the interested is limited, the security assumption are not simple, and it would be extremely simple for someone that needs that (and understand the consequences) to implement it itself. Thus I'm not really sure it should be part of our contracts.\r\n\r\nSide note: for gas optimisation, you could remove the `isPrivate` variable and replace it with `code != bytes32(0)`",
